# Results-archive snapshots (#276b, sweeps/archive/snapshot.py) are per-run BACKTEST OUTPUTS,
# not source. Each run writes <config_hash>/<backtest_id>/{result.json, trades.jsonl.gz}. These
# are the durable learn-substrate (the #303 mine consumes them) but they are NOT git-tracked —
# they are regenerated by re-running the snapshotter and would otherwise bloat the repo. The
# directory itself is kept (this .gitignore) so persist_run's dest_root resolves on a fresh clone.
*
!.gitignore
# The candidates/ subdir (#303 (B) signal-winner populations) carries its OWN .gitignore + README
# that must survive a fresh clone — un-ignore the dir so git descends into it and that nested
# .gitignore (which tracks README + ignores the regenerable <year>.jsonl) takes effect.
!candidates/
